{"tid":2195604,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"CNN：習近平唔會介意美國唔再叫佢President Xi，因為佢將要成為Chairman of CCP 黨主席","createTime":"2020-09-09T09:30:30.000Z","updateTime":"2020-10-11T16:59:51.000Z","uid":155095,"like":15,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":20,"replies":[{"pid":"b2e59d00f64b87525813c3dab5b481a00940a9ef","tid":2195604,"uid":155095,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-09T09:30:30.000Z","msg":"source: <a href=\"https://edition.cnn.com/2020/09/08/asia/xi-jinping-title-us-bill-intl-dst-hnk/index.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2020%2F09%2F08%2Fasia%2Fxi-jinping-title-us-bill-intl-dst-hnk%2Findex.html&d=Yvf7L03l0%2FKFASkGPCPwg3hUmc0vP2awQoWdJLgJf%2FY%3D&h=247cf614\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2020%2F09%2F08%2Fasia%2Fxi-jinping-title-us-bill-intl-dst-hnk%2Findex.html&h=7f0d9fc6\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://edition.cnn.com/2020/09/08/asia/xi-jinping-title-us-bill-intl-dst-hnk/index.html</a><br />\n<br />\nUS lawmakers want to stop calling Xi Jinping a President. But will he care?<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://cdn.cnn.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/200903102151-080220-xi-jiping-titles-illustration-large-169.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.cnn.com%2Fcnnnext%2Fdam%2Fassets%2F200903102151-080220-xi-jiping-titles-illustration-large-169.jpg&h=5a7f1ff8&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\nNow a new bill in the United States Congress wants to <span class=\"blue\">strip Xi of the title &quot;President,&quot;</span> which most Western governments and English-language news organizations -- including CNN -- refer to him by.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;China is not a democracy, and its citizens have no right to vote, assemble, or speak freely,&quot; said the US-China Economic and Security Review Commission, a US government panel,&nbsp;in a 2019 report to Congress. &quot;<span class=\"green\">Giving General Secretary Xi the unearned title of 'President'</span> lends a veneer of democratic legitimacy to the CCP and Xi's authoritarian rule.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nIn the past two months alone, FBI Director&nbsp;Christopher Wray,&nbsp;US Attorney General&nbsp;William Barr,&nbsp;National Security Advisor&nbsp;Robert O'Brien&nbsp;and Secretary of State&nbsp;Mike Pompeo&nbsp;have <span class=\"green\">all referred to Xi by the title of General Secretary</span> in speeches and statements -- a clear departure from the White House's previous practice of referring to the Chinese leader as &quot;President Xi.&quot;<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://api.time.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/chairmanxi_0411_intcover.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.time.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F03%2Fchairmanxi_0411_intcover.jpg&h=19d7625e&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n&quot;This year we can see a lot of steps (by Xi) in preparation for the coming 20th Party Congress (scheduled for 2022), but also we could see such <span class=\"red\">change in the English title of Chairman</span>,&quot; said Wu Qiang, a political commentator in Beijing. &quot;<span class=\"red\">The title of Chairman means the top, absolute top</span>, absolute authority. The totalitarian title for the leader of the Party.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nIf Xi brings the title back, it would be his most significant step in following Mao's legacy, Wu Qiang added -- a sign that &quot;he wants to turn back to the Maoist era.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nAnd adopting the term &quot;Chairman&quot; could help Xi consolidate even more power, said Leung -- perhaps turning him, literally, into the <span class=\"red\">Chairman of Everything</span>.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bFisyWJZDUE\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DbFisyWJZDUE&d=Yvf7L03l0%2FKFASkGPCPwg3hUmc0vP2awQoWdJLgJf%2FY%3D&h=53160470\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bFisyWJZDUE</a>"},{"pid":"8030bdb256b68fdb42bd0ca9597ac1ca6aba286d","tid":2195604,"uid":82359,"like":33,"dislike":0,"score":33,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-09-09T09:31:20.000Z","msg":"係因為佢唔識英文"},{"pid":"046af9aa8074fc48a3a1c16a75805a8d11d34d14","tid":2195604,"uid":373220,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-09T09:34:22.000Z","msg":"叫佢獨裁者"},{"pid":"d70524170a8415f7a910d6db4586a59b82bd8f49","tid":2195604,"uid":161684,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-09T09:35:55.000Z","msg":"其實相當公道<br />\n最好幫埋佢稱帝<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"a72b7d744cf9cced440d8cc49305e4d2865830a7","tid":2195604,"uid":25468,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-09T09:36:29.000Z","msg":"重點唔係要習大大介意 , 而係避免外間誤會佢係民選領袖"},{"pid":"73ecaf2671202e15b99b6b9a4031d17571c4a852","tid":2195604,"uid":511,"like":8,"dislike":0,"score":8,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-09-09T09:36:51.000Z","msg":"Heil Xitler<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"b53ca691c50dc87c18a0ad0d118e04268c97dbdd","tid":2195604,"uid":3241,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-09-09T09:37:02.000Z","msg":"5000蚊主席"},{"pid":"caae705e6a76104b5832f9760057c3c165cee578","tid":2195604,"uid":251732,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-09T09:37:05.000Z","msg":"完全合情合理 因為小熊維尼定定就係呢一個黑幫式政黨嘅首領"},{"pid":"0f94d568f6c3e8b4db9b8c9e6494b3537366cd6a","tid":2195604,"uid":251732,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"73ecaf2671202e15b99b6b9a4031d17571c4a852","tid":2195604,"uid":511,"like":8,"dislike":0,"score":8,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-09-09T09:36:51.000Z","msg":"Heil Xitler<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-09T09:37:19.000Z","msg":"Jinping Akbar"},{"pid":"2f3d0f8d687b5bc3ba55a697a4f24bd0d016f517","tid":2195604,"uid":44646,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"quote":{"pid":"8030bdb256b68fdb42bd0ca9597ac1ca6aba